        " applied the mathematical methods of Gibbs to the analysis of chemical processes.         The etymology of thermodynamics has an intricate history.  It was first spelled in a hyphenated form as an adjective  and from 1854 to 1868 as the noun thermo-dynamics to represent the science of generalized heat engines.     American ": null
